snippet.textDisplay:
Well yeah, overall the S20 Ultra is a little better. It's newer, so that makes sense.


In daylight I still prefer the iPhone. Better dynamic range, stabilization (see other videos), colors, faster focusing, better skin tones and less smoothing.
At night-time, the Samsung is better in most cases. It has a bigger sensor and u get night mode on the ultrawide lens as well. The front-facing camera is better in low light also. The zoom is much better, but I would only go up to 30x. If u go more than that, the picture doesn't look good in my opinion. Sound recording also goes to Samsung (other videos).
I wouldn't shoot at 8K unless I was using a tripod. The stabilization looks horrible, it takes up a lot of memory and it's cropped in.


That said, S20 Ultra is huge. I wouldn't buy a phone that big. For me, the small iPhone 11 Pro would be the right choice, since I like using it with one hand and I sometimes put it in the pocket of my pants.
Before you say anything: yes, I'm an iPhone user.
